<subSubSection id="C365655CD008FFAA929F292FA777F9C9" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC036D7D008FFAA929F292FA777F9C9" blockId="8.[178,1086,1149,1597]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">
Remark: In the coll. Berlin is an old 
<taxonomicName id="4C7F4D54D008FFAA90A8292FA181FAA8" box="[645,735,1351,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ferreola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90BEAC5D008FFAA90A8292FA181FAA8" box="[645,735,1351,1372]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Ferreola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male with an handwritten label &quot; 
<emphasis id="B90BEAC5D008FFAA9291290BA3A5FA8C" box="[188,251,1379,1400]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">barrei</emphasis>
&quot; and a red printed &quot; 
<typeStatus id="54C48875D008FFAA93C2290BA140FA8C" box="[495,542,1379,1400]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">type</typeStatus>
&quot; label. It agree perfect with the (short) original description of 
<emphasis id="B90BEAC5D008FFAA936B2917A176FA60" box="[326,552,1407,1428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Pseudoferreola barrei</emphasis>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEE4B26D008FFAA907D2917A01FFA61" author="RADOSZKOWSKI O" box="[592,833,1407,1429]" journalOrPublisher="Horae So c. Ent. Rossica" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" pagination="38 - 81" part="27" refId="ref10436" refString="RADOSZKOWSKI O. (1893): Faune hymenopterologique transcaspienne. - Horae So c. Ent. Rossica: 27: 38 - 81." title="Faune hymenopterologique transcaspienne" type="journal article" year="1893">RADOSZKOWSKI (1893)</bibRefCitation>
. For that reason we treat it as the 
<typeStatus id="54C48875D008FFAA933429F3A22CFA45" box="[281,370,1435,1457]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7F4D54D008FFAA93B229F3A11BFA44" baseAuthorityName="Radoszkowski" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[415,581,1435,1456]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ferreola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barrei">
<emphasis id="B90BEAC5D008FFAA93B229F3A11BFA44" box="[415,581,1435,1456]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Ferreola barrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species is valid and represent a hitherto unknown Central Asian 
<taxonomicName id="4C7F4D54D008FFAA93EE29DFA143FA38" box="[451,541,1463,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ferreola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90BEAC5D008FFAA93EE29DFA143FA38" box="[451,541,1463,1484]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Ferreola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7F4D54D008FFAA90C729D0A02EFA38" baseAuthorityName="Kohl" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[746,880,1463,1485]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ferreola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orchesica">
<emphasis id="B90BEAC5D008FFAA90C729D0A02EFA38" box="[746,880,1463,1485]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">F. orchesica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the western Mediterranean area. The female is still unknown, but we can assign some males from 
<collectingCountry id="F3687647D008FFAA929F2987A385F9F0" box="[178,219,1519,1540]" name="Iran" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Iran</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3687647D008FFAA93352987A2CAF9F1" box="[280,404,1519,1541]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
with the 
<typeStatus id="54C48875D008FFAA90292987A16EF9F0" box="[516,560,1519,1540]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7F4D54D008FFAA90702998A1E0F9F0" baseAuthorityName="Radoszkowski" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[605,702,1519,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ferreola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barrei">
<emphasis id="B90BEAC5D008FFAA90702998A1E0F9F0" box="[605,702,1519,1541]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">F. barrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus id="54C48875D008FFAA91292987A06EF9F0" box="[772,816,1519,1540]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">type</typeStatus>
location &quot;Serax&quot; is now Serakhs or Sarahs in southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3687647D008FFAA90252A63A1CBF9D5" box="[520,661,1547,1569]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
at 
<geoCoordinate id="EE4B5010D008FFAA90EF2A63A052F9D5" box="[706,780,1547,1569]" degrees="36.53" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" precision="555" value="36.53">36.53N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE4B5010D008FFAA91372A63A03CF9D5" box="[794,866,1547,1569]" degrees="61.22" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" precision="555" value="61.22">61.22E</geoCoordinate>
(A. Antropov pers. comm.). A. Antropov also agree that the label most probably is from O. Radoszkowski.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
